reviewText: Yes more XY is coming out this series is a good step up from the previous and does a better job giving Ashes friends more character development and episode focus...Sure it took Serena a while to figure out her own goal path but alot of us struggle to find one glad she did and I enjoy the friendship better with these guys with Ash........

Ash's journey continues through the Kalos Region! First Ash meets the Champion of Kalos, Diantha! Then its the Pokemon Summer Academy with new rivals Tierno, Shauna, and Trevor! Finally Ash has his 3rd Gym Match VS Korrina of the Shalour Gym! Can he defeat her Mega Lucario? Plus Ash, Serena, and Clemont add new Pokemon to their team! Enjoy 24 episodes in this action packed series!

The copy of this I received was a used, refurbished copy originally from a library.  Disks 1 and 3 worked fine, but disk 2 played only half way through before it stopped functioning and shut my player down.  Nothing I did would get it to work.  My advise: Buy new if you want to ensure the purchase plays.

I saw a review saying "beware only half the epsiodes" or whatever. That's completely misleading. When you cross reference the episodes to what has aired  (Google Pokemon XY episode guide, look for wikipedia) they match as far as American releases. For the whole Kalos region episodes you will need to purchase the XY:Kalos Quest sets and XYZ sets. The other review is misleading as a "complete series" won't correct it when the Kalos Region are broken into 3 separate series. The Bublagarden websites also has the lists of dvds available for purchase from EVERY season broken down in original release to re-release.
Very pleased with my dvds. My family enjoyed it and cannot wait for XYZ
